article.linkText: Turner scores 17 off the bench, San Diego downs Portland 71-66
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- — Deuce Turner scored 17 points off the bench to help lead San Diego past Portland 71-66 on Thursday night. Turner added six rebounds for the Toreros (16-11, 6-6 West Coast Conference). PJ Hayes had 14 points and Kevin Patton Jr. scored 13. Tyler Harris finished with 19 points, 10 rebounds and three steals for the Pilots (9-18, 3-9). Bol Dengdit added 15 points, 10 rebounds and four assists. Tyler Robertson had 13 points, eight rebounds and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
